Former Kaduna Central Senator Shehu Sani has highlighted eight things the next President must do. In a tweet via his verified Twitter page on Wednesday, Senator Sani said the next Nigerian leader must combat terrorism, fix the economy, unite the nation, fix the power sector, and service the country’s debt, among others. He tweeted, “Eight to-do list for Nigeria’s next president. Meanwhile, the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), Bola Tinubu, Atiku Abubakar of the PDP, Peter Obi of the Labour Party (LP), and Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso of the New Nigeria Peoples Party (NNPP) are hoping to succeed President Muhammadu Buhari in 2023.